         Features to be added to Amiga FreeCell

This list is in no particular order. Unless I get lots of emails badgering
me to fix something I'm just going to do whichever ones irritate me at the
time.

Record statistics on games won/lost
Save and Load statistics files
Specify Statistics file as a tooltype / command line option
Draw pretty pictures (or at least suits) on the cards
Draw rounded corners on the cards
Support NTSC 200 line screen modes (prob. with a scrollbar)
Support Display mode requester for WB2.1+
Support fonts other than Topaz 8 for menu/requester text
Add an option to select specific games
Display a game number and allow restarting a specific game
Automatically move a whole block of cards between rows if enough free cells
Allow the user to define the colours
Call LoadRGB32 rather than LoadRGB4 on WB3+ machines to set colour map
Add an AmigaGuide help file
Move cards to next free cell on double click
Design a pretty icon
